By: Al-'Arabi al-Hasanî ad-Darqâwî
---
Spiritual perception (al-man'â) is very subtle; one can only retain it
with the aid of the senses (al-hiss), and one can only make it last
through spiritual conversation (almudakkara), invocation {ad-dikr) and
the breaking of natural habits.
